description:
For those who got a copy of “Filipino Vegan”🙂 : No need to use QR codes to see photos of the other recipes in the book. You can now access them on AstigVegan.com and click on the drop-down menu, as you can see here. Each dish will direct you to its own designated photo.

The idea of not printing photos for every recipe in the book came from not wanting to publish an expensive coffee table book that not everyone in the Philippines can afford. We want to make this book accessible and approachable to as many Filipinos here as much as possible. 

From the ingredients to the procedures, down to the cost of the actual book, we consciously and thoughtfully made sure it’s for every walk of life. 

Although the initial idea was to create QR codes, we realized they weren’t executed the way we envisioned it. So, to remedy this, we’ve uploaded the photos on the website for you to access anytime as a reference. 

We understand that photos can be extremely helpful in guiding you through the recipe, especially if you’re unfamiliar with the dish so we hope you find this helpful. If you have any questions or feedback, please don’t hesitate to message me. I’m always looking forward to hearing from you. Take care!

#veganinthephilippines #veganfinds #astigvegan #filipinovegan #veganfilipino #vegan
